---
description: Security rules for all CopelandOS changes
alwaysApply: true
---

- `worker.js` is the canonical Cloudflare Worker entry point.
- Do not add features before security tasks in `docs/cursor-ready-issues.md`.
- Never commit secrets, tokens, OAuth codes, refresh tokens, real email content, `.env`, or `.dev.vars`.
- Keep browser CORS restricted to the exact configured `ALLOWED_ORIGIN`; CORS is not authentication.
- Gmail operations are draft-only. Do not call the Gmail messages send endpoint.
- Add or update tests for every security behavior change.
- Do not weaken tests or expose upstream error bodies that may contain sensitive information.
- Open a branch and draft PR; do not push directly to `main`.
